Commercial work is crowding out your personal projects. MindWell carries the majority of your workspace commits, which means your engineering effort has shifted toward paid work and away from the exploratory or foundational projects you might otherwise be building.

This matters because it shapes what you're learning, what gets maintained, and what technical debt you're accumulating. If MindWell is consuming most of your attention, your other repositories are likely getting lighter maintenance or slower iteration—which can feel invisible until you notice a gap months later.
